Today is 18th september,
=> HTML Entities
- Reserved characters in HTML must be replaced with character entities.
- Characters that are not present on your keyboard can also be replaced by entities.
- A common character entity used in HTML is the non-breaking space: &nbsp;
- A non-breaking space is a space that will not break into a new line.
- For some other useful HTML character entities you have to go this link => https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_entities.asp

=> HTML Charset
- To display HTML page correctly, a web browser must known which character set to use.
- ASCII was the first character encoding standard (also called character set). ASCII defined 128 different alphanumeric characters.
- ANSI character set support 256 different character.
- ISO-8859-1 was the default character set for HTML 4. This character set also supported 256 different character codes.

